      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TYCOON DREAMER (5) gets the blinkers on this time after a 2.8L defeat at Belmont a fortnight ago. Chris Parnham remains in the saddle and she's open to plenty of improvement third-up. Fresh run suggested she was ready to go to the next level this time around and this presents as the one to beat. EARL IT IS (1) was a touch disappointing over the 1000m journey at Belmont most recently and rises up to 1200m once again today. He's 0/3 at this trip, but this shapes as a suitable assignment with O'Donnell replacing the apprentice hoop. Can swoop late to return to winning ways. MR KISSINGER (2) pulled up with a slight issue when racing in much stronger company last time out. Back to an easier race here and Pike hops back on board having guided him to victory previously. Maps beautifully and can get the job done this time. MELODY FAIR (6) showed enough on debut to suggest she can be in the finish. ROSENTREA (3) will take plenty of catching from the front.",
